WEBVTT

1
00:00:55.573 --> 00:00:58.926
You don't like flyin', do you?

2
00:00:58.950 --> 00:01:02.078
What gives you that idea?

3
00:01:03.247 --> 00:01:07.811
You wanna know the secret
to surviving air travel?

4
00:01:07.835 --> 00:01:11.065
After you get where you're going,
take off your shoes and your socks.

5
00:01:11.089 --> 00:01:15.925
Then you walk around on the rug barefoot
and make fists with your toes.

6
00:01:16.886 --> 00:01:19.114
Fists with your toes?

7
00:01:19.138 --> 00:01:21.575
I know, I know. It sounds crazy.

8
00:01:21.599 --> 00:01:23.660
Trust me. I've been doin' it
for nine years.

9
00:01:23.684 --> 00:01:26.789
Yes, sir. Better than a shower
and a hot cup of coffee.

10
00:01:26.813 --> 00:01:29.564
Okay.

11
00:01:39.158 --> 00:01:41.284
It's okay. I'm a cop.

12
00:01:43.913 --> 00:01:47.351
Trust me. I've been
doin' this for 11 years.

13
00:01:47.375 --> 00:01:49.936
On behalf of your captain and crew...

14
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:52.689
we'd like to welcome you
to Los Angeles.

15
00:01:52.713 --> 00:01:55.131
Have a very Merry Christmas.

16
00:02:04.350 --> 00:02:09.706
Flight 247 to Tucson
now boarding at Gate 14.

17
00:02:09.730 --> 00:02:14.609
Flight 247 to Tucson
now boarding at Gate 14.

18
00:02:17.363 --> 00:02:21.616
Mr. Edward Machowski,
please report to the white courtesy phone.

19
00:02:27.080 --> 00:02:29.059
Ah.

20
00:02:29.083 --> 00:02:31.334
How do you do?

21
00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:47.452
Ladies and gentlemen!
Ladies and gentlemen!

22
00:02:47.476 --> 00:02:50.122
I want to congratulate
each and every one of you...

23
00:02:50.146 --> 00:02:54.649
for making this one of the greatest years
in the history of the Nakatomi Corporation.

24
00:02:58.112 --> 00:03:03.385
On behalf of the chief executive officer,
Mr. Ozu, and the board of directors...

25
00:03:03.409 --> 00:03:08.037
we thank you, one and all, and wish you
a Merry Christmas and a happy New Year!

26
00:03:11.792 --> 00:03:15.439
Hey, Holly, what about
dinner tonight, huh?

27
00:03:15.463 --> 00:03:17.941
Harry, it's Christmas Eve.

28
00:03:17.965 --> 00:03:21.217
Families, stockings.

29
00:03:22.260 --> 00:03:24.239
Chestnuts.

30
00:03:24.263 --> 00:03:26.408
Rudolph and Frosty.

31
00:03:26.432 --> 00:03:28.452
Any of these things ring a bell?

32
00:03:28.476 --> 00:03:33.332
Actually, I was thinkin' more of
mulled wine, a nice aged Brie...

33
00:03:33.356 --> 00:03:35.334
and a roaring fireplace.

34
00:03:35.358 --> 00:03:38.151
You know what I'm sayin'?

35
00:03:40.196 --> 00:03:43.592
Ginny, it's 5:40. Go join the party.
Have some champagne.

36
00:03:43.616 --> 00:03:46.220
You're makin' me feel
like Ebenezer Scrooge.

37
00:03:46.244 --> 00:03:49.890
Thanks a lot, Ms. Gennero. Do you
think the baby can handle a little sip?

38
00:03:49.914 --> 00:03:52.809
That baby's ready to tend bar.

39
00:03:52.833 --> 00:03:54.853
Last chance.

40
00:03:54.877 --> 00:03:57.962
Bye.

41
00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:05.739
McClane residence.
Lucy McClane speaking.

42
00:04:05.763 --> 00:04:10.160
Hello, Lucy McClane.
This is your mother speaking.

43
00:04:10.184 --> 00:04:13.246
Mommy! When are you coming home?

44
00:04:13.270 --> 00:04:17.626
Pretty soon. Pretty soon.
You'll be in bed when I get there though.

45
00:04:17.650 --> 00:04:20.212
Let me talk to Paulina, okay, hon?

46
00:04:20.236 --> 00:04:24.383
And no snoopin' around the house
looking for presents.

47
00:04:24.407 --> 00:04:27.116
Is Daddy coming home with you?

48
00:04:29.078 --> 00:04:33.225
Well, we'll see what
Santa and Mommy can do, okay?

49
00:04:33.249 --> 00:04:35.310
Put Paulina on. Bye, honey.

50
00:04:35.334 --> 00:04:37.502
Paulina!

51
00:04:42.383 --> 00:04:44.361
Hola, Mrs. Holly.

52
00:04:44.385 --> 00:04:47.656
Um, did Mr. McClane call?

53
00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:51.368
No, Mrs. Holly. No telefonó.

54
00:04:51.392 --> 00:04:54.371
Well, he probably just didn't
have time before his flight.

55
00:04:54.395 --> 00:04:58.458
Um, it might be a good idea
to make up the spare bedroom just in case.

56
00:04:58.482 --> 00:05:01.211
Sí, Mrs. Holly.
I do that already.

57
00:05:01.235 --> 00:05:03.987
What would I do
without you, Paulina?

58
00:05:29.013 --> 00:05:31.180
California.

59
00:05:41.817 --> 00:05:43.795
Excuse me.

60
00:05:43.819 --> 00:05:45.881
Hey, I'm John McClane.

61
00:05:45.905 --> 00:05:49.032
Argyle. I'm your limo driver.

62
00:05:51.035 --> 00:05:53.369
Nice bear.

63
00:05:57.458 --> 00:06:01.772
Okay, Argyle. What do we do now?

64
00:06:01.796 --> 00:06:04.274
I was, uh, hopin' you could tell me.

65
00:06:04.298 --> 00:06:06.693
It's my first time drivin' a limo.

66
00:06:06.717 --> 00:06:09.905
Oh, that's okay. It's my
first time ridin' in one.

67
00:06:09.929 --> 00:06:12.783
Relax. We got everything
in this mug, man.

68
00:06:12.807 --> 00:06:16.286
Look at this - CD, C.B., TV...

69
00:06:16.310 --> 00:06:20.248
telephone, full bar, VHS.

70
00:06:20.272 --> 00:06:23.941
If your friend's hot to trot, I know a
few mama bears we can hook up with.

71
00:06:25.778 --> 00:06:28.340
- Or is he married?
- He's married.

72
00:06:28.364 --> 00:06:30.615
Okay.

73
00:06:31.492 --> 00:06:34.805
Oh, sorry about that.
It's the girl's day off.

74
00:06:34.829 --> 00:06:37.808
I didn't know you were
gonna sit up front.

75
00:06:37.832 --> 00:06:39.851
So, uh, your lady live out here?

76
00:06:39.875 --> 00:06:41.978
About the past six months.

77
00:06:42.002 --> 00:06:45.065
Meaning you still live in New York.

78
00:06:45.089 --> 00:06:48.485
You always ask this
many questions, Argyle?

79
00:06:48.509 --> 00:06:52.261
Sorry, man. I used to drive a cab, and, uh,
people would expect a little chitchat.

80
00:06:53.180 --> 00:06:56.493
- So, you divorced?
- Just drive the car, man.

81
00:06:56.517 --> 00:07:00.645
Hey, come on. You divorced?
You separated? She beat you up?

82
00:07:03.649 --> 00:07:07.336
He had a good job.
Turned into a great career.

83
00:07:07.360 --> 00:07:10.256
Ah, that meant she had to move here.

84
00:07:10.280 --> 00:07:12.509
You're very fast, Argyle.

85
00:07:12.533 --> 00:07:15.451
So why didn't you come?

86
00:07:17.455 --> 00:07:20.289
Well, why didn't you come
with her, man? What's up?

87
00:07:21.542 --> 00:07:23.520
'Cause I'm a New York cop.

88
00:07:23.544 --> 00:07:25.579
I got a six-month backlog of New York
scumbags

89
00:07:25.603 --> 00:07:27.023
I'm still trying to put behind bars.

90
00:07:27.047 --> 00:07:29.234
I can't just pick up
and go that easy.

91
00:07:29.258 --> 00:07:31.736
In other words, you thought
she wasn't gonna make it out here...

92
00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:33.738
and she'd come crawling
on back to you...

93
00:07:33.762 --> 00:07:36.366
so why bother to pack, right?

94
00:07:36.390 --> 00:07:38.785
Like I said,
you're very fast, Argyle.

95
00:07:38.809 --> 00:07:41.144
You mind if we hear some tunes?

96
00:07:44.148 --> 00:07:47.817
Hey, that'll work.

97
00:07:48.903 --> 00:07:51.006
Don't you got any Christmas music?

98
00:07:51.030 --> 00:07:54.157
This is Christmas music.

99
00:08:22.853 --> 00:08:26.500
So your lady sees you, you run into
each other's arms, the music comes up...

100
00:08:26.524 --> 00:08:29.211
and you live happily
ever after, right?

101
00:08:29.235 --> 00:08:32.214
I can live with that.

102
00:08:32.238 --> 00:08:35.759
So if it doesn't work out, man,
you got a place to stay?

103
00:08:35.783 --> 00:08:39.262
- I'll find a place.
- I tell you what.

104
00:08:39.286 --> 00:08:41.973
I'm gonna pull in
the parking garage and I'll wait.

105
00:08:41.997 --> 00:08:44.266
You score, you give me a call
on the car phone.

106
00:08:44.290 --> 00:08:46.269
I'll take your bags to the desk.

107
00:08:46.293 --> 00:08:48.646
You strike out,
I'll get you a hotel.

108
00:08:48.670 --> 00:08:50.899
You're all right, Argyle.

109
00:08:50.923 --> 00:08:54.050
Just remember that
when you sign for the tip.

110
00:09:16.990 --> 00:09:18.969
Hi.

111
00:09:18.993 --> 00:09:21.846
- Good evening.
- I'm here to see Holly McClane.

112
00:09:21.870 --> 00:09:24.121
Just type it in there.

113
00:09:29.003 --> 00:09:31.273
Cute toy.

114
00:09:31.297 --> 00:09:34.924
Yeah. You have to take a leak,
it'll even help you find your zipper.

115
00:09:50.899 --> 00:09:53.150
Christ.

116
00:09:57.573 --> 00:09:59.634
13th floor.

117
00:09:59.658 --> 00:10:02.636
The party. They're the only ones
left in the building.

118
00:10:02.660 --> 00:10:06.516
Take the express elevator.
Get off where you hear the noise.

119
00:10:06.540 --> 00:10:08.708
Thanks.

120
00:11:05.974 --> 00:11:08.893
- Champagne, sir?
- Yeah. Thanks.

121
00:11:43.637 --> 00:11:45.615
Oh, I'm sorry.

122
00:11:45.639 --> 00:11:48.391
Hey! Merry Christmas!

123
00:11:51.310 --> 00:11:55.959
Jesus. Fuckin' California.

124
00:11:55.983 --> 00:11:58.169
I couldn't agree with you more.

125
00:11:58.193 --> 00:12:00.403
Why don't I talk to him right now?

126
00:12:01.363 --> 00:12:03.341
Hi. I'm looking for, uh -

127
00:12:03.365 --> 00:12:05.343
- Holly Gennero.
- Yeah.

128
00:12:05.367 --> 00:12:06.944
Then you must be John McClane.

129
00:12:06.968 --> 00:12:08.722
- Joe Takagi.
- Hi.

130
00:12:08.746 --> 00:12:10.806
- How was your ride in?
- Nice.

131
00:12:10.830 --> 00:12:14.185
- I have you to thank for that?
- It seemed the least we could do.

132
00:12:14.209 --> 00:12:16.186
It's quite a place you have here.

133
00:12:16.210 --> 00:12:18.273
It will be
if we ever get it finished.

134
00:12:18.297 --> 00:12:20.442
There are still several
floors under construction.

135
00:12:20.466 --> 00:12:24.112
Holly went to the vault room to fax some
documents. She should be back any minute.

136
00:12:24.136 --> 00:12:26.762
In the meanwhile,
her office is right back here.

137
00:12:28.766 --> 00:12:31.225
Ellis.

138
00:12:33.060 --> 00:12:36.249
I was just makin' a call,
and this was, uh, the nearest phone.

139
00:12:36.273 --> 00:12:39.942
I want you to meet
John McClane, Holly's husband.

140
00:12:41.236 --> 00:12:44.924
Holly's policeman. Ellis is in charge
of international development.

141
00:12:44.948 --> 00:12:47.343
Heard a heck of a lot about you.

142
00:12:47.367 --> 00:12:49.577
Missed some.

143
00:12:51.413 --> 00:12:56.019
Uh, could I get you anything? Food,
cake, uh, some watered-down champagne?

144
00:12:56.043 --> 00:12:59.105
No, thank you. I'm fine.

145
00:12:59.129 --> 00:13:02.108
You throw quite a party.

146
00:13:02.132 --> 00:13:04.861
I didn't realize they
celebrated Christmas in Japan.

147
00:13:04.885 --> 00:13:09.680
Hey, we're flexible. Pearl Harbor didn't
work out, so we got you with tape decks.

148
00:13:12.184 --> 00:13:14.803
Actually, it's kind of sort of a double
celebration.

149
00:13:14.827 --> 00:13:16.039
We, uh, closed a pretty big deal today.

150
00:13:16.063 --> 00:13:17.999
And a lot of it was due to Holly.

151
00:13:18.023 --> 00:13:19.876
- Am I right, Jo-Jo?
- Go ahead without me.

152
00:13:19.900 --> 00:13:22.777
I'll be about 4 minutes.

153
00:13:25.656 --> 00:13:27.907
John.

154
00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:32.889
Have you met everyone?

155
00:13:32.913 --> 00:13:35.225
No, we've been sticking him
with spears.

156
00:13:35.249 --> 00:13:37.393
Of course he has.

157
00:13:37.417 --> 00:13:40.104
She was made for the business.
Tough as nails.

158
00:13:40.128 --> 00:13:44.025
- Yeah.
- I was hoping you made that flight.

159
00:13:44.049 --> 00:13:46.694
Show him the watch.

160
00:13:46.718 --> 00:13:47.753
Later.

161
00:13:47.777 --> 00:13:49.989
Well, go on. Show him.
What, are you embarrassed?

162
00:13:50.013 --> 00:13:54.118
It's just a small token
of appreciation for all her hard work.

163
00:13:54.142 --> 00:13:56.204
It's a Rolex.

164
00:13:56.228 --> 00:13:58.248
I'm sure I'll see it later.

165
00:13:58.272 --> 00:14:00.583
Is there a place
where I could wash up?

166
00:14:00.607 --> 00:14:03.317
Sure.

167
00:14:18.458 --> 00:14:21.710
You'll have to forgive Ellis.
He gets very depressed this time of year.

168
00:14:23.005 --> 00:14:25.984
He thought he was
God's greatest gift, you know?

169
00:14:26.008 --> 00:14:28.278
Yeah, I know the type.

170
00:14:28.302 --> 00:14:31.446
I think he's got his eye on you.

171
00:14:31.470 --> 00:14:35.451
It's okay. I have my eye
on his private bathroom.

172
00:14:35.475 --> 00:14:37.620
Where you staying?

173
00:14:37.644 --> 00:14:41.541
Things happened so fast, I didn't
get a chance to ask you on the phone.

174
00:14:41.565 --> 00:14:45.295
- Cappy Roberts retired out here.
- Oh, yeah?

175
00:14:45.319 --> 00:14:48.506
- Told me I could bunk in with him.
- Cappy retired, huh?

176
00:14:48.530 --> 00:14:50.758
- Where's he live?
- "Ramona."

177
00:14:50.782 --> 00:14:52.926
Pomona.

178
00:14:52.950 --> 00:14:55.596
- Huh?
- Pomona.

179
00:14:55.620 --> 00:14:58.516
- Pomona.
- Yeah.

180
00:14:58.540 --> 00:15:02.020
God, you'll be in the car
half the time.

181
00:15:02.044 --> 00:15:05.648
Why don't we make it easy?
I have a spare bedroom.

182
00:15:05.672 --> 00:15:08.568
I mean, it's not huge
or anything, but...

183
00:15:08.592 --> 00:15:12.261
the kids would love
to have you at the house.

184
00:15:13.013 --> 00:15:16.390
They would, huh?

185
00:15:18.018 --> 00:15:20.455
I would too.

186
00:15:20.479 --> 00:15:22.999
Oh! Ooh!

187
00:15:23.023 --> 00:15:25.274
Sorry.

188
00:15:32.074 --> 00:15:34.783
I missed you.

189
00:15:40.958 --> 00:15:43.102
I guess you didn't miss
my name, though, huh?

190
00:15:43.126 --> 00:15:47.148
Except maybe when
you're signing checks?

191
00:15:47.172 --> 00:15:49.465
Since when did you
start using "Ms. Gennero"?

192
00:15:52.469 --> 00:15:55.740
This is a Japanese company. They
figure a married woman's got one foot -

193
00:15:55.764 --> 00:15:57.992
You are a married woman, Holly.
You're married to me.

194
00:15:58.016 --> 00:16:00.954
Are we gonna have this conversation again?
We did this in July.

195
00:16:00.978 --> 00:16:03.246
- We never finished this conversation in July.
- I had an opportunity.

196
00:16:03.270 --> 00:16:05.666
- I had to take it.
- Right. No matter what the consequences...

197
00:16:05.690 --> 00:16:07.876
no matter what it did to our marriage,
you had to.

198
00:16:07.900 --> 00:16:10.922
It didn't do anything except maybe change
your idea of what our marriage should be.

199
00:16:10.946 --> 00:16:13.925
I don't think you have a clue what my idea
of our marriage should be.

200
00:16:13.949 --> 00:16:16.469
I know exactly what your idea
of our marriage should be.

201
00:16:16.493 --> 00:16:18.494
Ms. Gennero, I -

202
00:16:19.997 --> 00:16:23.832
- Excuse me.
- Hi.

203
00:16:24.835 --> 00:16:27.021
Um, Mr. Takagi is looking for you.

204
00:16:27.045 --> 00:16:29.581
He-He wants you to say
something to the troops.

205
00:16:29.605 --> 00:16:30.673
Thank you.

206
00:16:35.053 --> 00:16:39.932
Speech time.
Be back in a few minutes.

207
00:16:50.777 --> 00:16:53.006
That's great, John.

208
00:16:53.030 --> 00:16:55.614
Good job. Very mature.

209
00:17:45.165 --> 00:17:48.311
So Kareem rebounds, right?
Feeds Worthy on the break.

210
00:17:48.335 --> 00:17:51.754
Over to A.C., to Magic,
then back to Worthy, right?

211
00:17:52.964 --> 00:17:55.674
Boom! Two points.

212
00:17:58.260 --> 00:18:00.429
We're in.

213
00:20:29.996 --> 00:20:32.247
Left.

214
00:20:34.250 --> 00:20:37.085
Right, and again left.

215
00:21:07.242 --> 00:21:10.035
Son of a bitch.

216
00:21:12.038 --> 00:21:14.206
Fists with your toes.

217
00:21:45.113 --> 00:21:47.091
Yeah, Argyle.

218
00:21:47.115 --> 00:21:50.176
- Hey, Mac! How's it goin' up there?
- Oh, all right. Where are you?

219
00:21:50.200 --> 00:21:53.222
I'm kickin' it in the garage. What's
the word with you and your lady, man?

220
00:21:53.246 --> 00:21:55.789
Uh, the vote's not in yet.

221
00:22:04.424 --> 00:22:06.861
- Hey Brother.
- Just a moment.

222
00:22:06.885 --> 00:22:09.052
No, no... not yet, just wait...

223
00:22:26.488 --> 00:22:28.466
Argyle?

224
00:22:28.490 --> 00:22:31.366
Mac, you there? Hello?

225
00:22:39.750 --> 00:22:42.210
You know the number. Use it!

226
00:24:14.012 --> 00:24:19.099
Stay calm. Everything's gonna be fine.
Everything's gonna be fine.

227
00:24:37.785 --> 00:24:40.036
Shit!

228
00:24:43.124 --> 00:24:45.834
Think. Think.

229
00:25:02.100 --> 00:25:08.231
Ladies and gentlemen.

230
00:25:14.989 --> 00:25:19.094
"Due to the Nakatomi Corporation's
legacy of greed around the globe...

231
00:25:19.118 --> 00:25:23.663
"they're about to be taught a lesson
in the real use of power.

232
00:25:24.790 --> 00:25:27.083
You will be witnesses."

233
00:25:29.045 --> 00:25:31.065
Now...

234
00:25:31.089 --> 00:25:33.256
where is Mr. Takagi?

235
00:25:35.677 --> 00:25:39.949
Joseph Yoshinobu Takagi.

236
00:25:39.973 --> 00:25:42.451
Born, Kyoto, 1937.

237
00:25:42.475 --> 00:25:44.453
Don't move.

238
00:25:44.477 --> 00:25:50.084
Family emigrated
to San Pedro, California, 1939.

239
00:25:50.108 --> 00:25:54.630
Interned at Manzanar, 1942 to '43.

240
00:25:54.654 --> 00:25:59.635
Scholarship student,
University of California...

241
00:25:59.659 --> 00:26:01.910
1955.

242
00:26:05.832 --> 00:26:10.646
Law degree, Stanford, 1962.

243
00:26:10.670 --> 00:26:15.484
M.B.A., Harvard, 1970.

244
00:26:15.508 --> 00:26:18.153
President, Nakatomi Trading.

245
00:26:18.177 --> 00:26:20.489
Vice Chairman,
Nakatomi Investment Group.

246
00:26:20.513 --> 00:26:22.722
Enough.

247
