494
00:56:55.805 --> 00:56:58.932
Everything here's okay. Over.

495
00:57:07.483 --> 00:57:10.443
Damn! Goddamn it!
Jesus H. Christ!

496
00:57:16.826 --> 00:57:19.054
Welcome to the party, pal!

497
00:57:19.078 --> 00:57:21.121
Goddamn it!

498
00:57:27.420 --> 00:57:29.898
Now means now, goddamn it!

499
00:57:29.922 --> 00:57:32.109
Policeman under automatic
rifle fire at Nakatomi!

500
00:57:32.133 --> 00:57:34.194
I need backup assistance now!

501
00:57:34.218 --> 00:57:37.095
Now, goddamn it! Now!

502
00:57:55.280 --> 00:57:58.010
Monica, I can get us a table.

503
00:57:58.034 --> 00:58:00.012
Wolfgang and I
are very close friends.

504
00:58:00.036 --> 00:58:02.014
Officer in need of assistance.

505
00:58:02.038 --> 00:58:04.141
- I interviewed him.
- Reports of shots fired at Nakatomi.

506
00:58:04.165 --> 00:58:06.143
2000 block, Avenue of the Stars.

507
00:58:06.167 --> 00:58:08.353
Repeat, officer
needs assistance at -

508
00:58:08.377 --> 00:58:11.606
I'm in Nakatomi Plaza.
They're turning my car into Swiss cheese!

509
00:58:11.630 --> 00:58:15.967
I need backup assistance now!
Now, goddamn it! Now!

510
00:58:36.739 --> 00:58:38.759
I never thought I'd love
to hear that sound.

511
00:58:38.783 --> 00:58:43.388
All of you, relax. This is a matter
of inconvenient timing, that's all.

512
00:58:43.412 --> 00:58:45.556
Police action was inevitable...

513
00:58:45.580 --> 00:58:48.435
and, as it happens, necessary.

514
00:58:48.459 --> 00:58:52.064
So let them fumble about
outside and stay calm.

515
00:58:52.088 --> 00:58:54.233
This is simply the beginning.

516
00:58:54.257 --> 00:58:58.654
I thought I told all of you
I want radio silence until further-

517
00:58:58.678 --> 00:59:01.406
Oh, I'm very sorry, Hans.
I didn't get that message.

518
00:59:01.430 --> 00:59:04.868
Maybe you should have
put it on the bulletin board.

519
00:59:04.892 --> 00:59:07.371
I figured since I waxed Tony and Marco
and his friend here...

520
00:59:07.395 --> 00:59:10.249
I figured you and Karl and Franco
might be a little lonely.

521
00:59:10.273 --> 00:59:12.416
So I wanted to give you a call.

522
00:59:12.440 --> 00:59:14.692
How does he know so much about -

523
00:59:16.320 --> 00:59:18.632
That's very kind of you.

524
00:59:18.656 --> 00:59:22.511
I assume you are
our mysterious party crasher.

525
00:59:22.535 --> 00:59:25.973
You are most troublesome
for a security guard.

526
00:59:25.997 --> 00:59:28.892
Sorry, Hans. Wrong guess.

527
00:59:28.916 --> 00:59:33.336
Would you like to go for "Double Jeopardy"
where the scores can really change?

528
00:59:37.008 --> 00:59:39.194
Hmm. These are very bad for you.

529
00:59:39.218 --> 00:59:41.613
Who are you then?

530
00:59:41.637 --> 00:59:45.450
Just a fly in the ointment, Hans.
A monkey in the wrench.

531
00:59:45.474 --> 00:59:48.268
A pain in the ass.

532
00:59:49.562 --> 00:59:52.583
Whoa.

533
00:59:52.607 --> 00:59:55.126
Check on all the others.
Don't use the radio.

534
00:59:55.150 --> 00:59:59.571
See if he's lying about Marco,
and find out if anyone else is missing.

535
01:00:02.950 --> 01:00:05.285
Mr. Mystery Guest...

536
01:00:06.454 --> 01:00:08.640
are you still there?

537
01:00:08.664 --> 01:00:13.145
Yeah, I'm still here. Unless you
wanna open the front door for me.

538
01:00:13.169 --> 01:00:15.146
No, I'm afraid not.

539
01:00:15.170 --> 01:00:17.858
But you have me at a loss.

540
01:00:17.882 --> 01:00:19.860
You know my name, but who are you?

541
01:00:19.884 --> 01:00:24.948
Just another American who saw
too many movies as a child?

542
01:00:24.972 --> 01:00:29.036
Another orphan of a bankrupt culture
who thinks he's John Wayne?

543
01:00:29.060 --> 01:00:31.913
Rambo? Marshal Dillon?

544
01:00:31.937 --> 01:00:35.166
I was always kind of partial
to Roy Rogers actually.

545
01:00:35.190 --> 01:00:37.169
I really liked those sequin shirts.

546
01:00:37.193 --> 01:00:40.653
Do you really think you have
a chance against us, Mr. Cowboy?

547
01:00:42.823 --> 01:00:46.159
Yippee-ki-yea, motherfucker.

548
01:00:49.580 --> 01:00:51.073
I can get the jump on everybody

549
01:00:51.097 --> 01:00:52.684
- if I get a remote.
- I don't have the new pages.

550
01:00:52.708 --> 01:00:56.229
- Where's the Gladden report?
- Harvey, keep your pants on, will you?

551
01:00:56.253 --> 01:00:57.413
Sam, look, I'm begging you.

552
01:00:57.437 --> 01:00:59.733
Simon's already at a remote thing
with that Santa sing-along.

553
01:00:59.757 --> 01:01:02.486
- I'll tell him to swing by.
- I'm not sitting on this for Simon!

554
01:01:02.510 --> 01:01:04.488
- I don't wanna hear it!
- This is my story!

555
01:01:04.512 --> 01:01:06.990
- I can't hear you.
- All right, look. Sam, I tell you what.

556
01:01:07.014 --> 01:01:09.910
You don't wanna give me a truck,
I'll go and I'll steal a truck.

557
01:01:09.934 --> 01:01:12.496
- Give us a break, Thornburg.
- Eat it, Harvey!

558
01:01:12.520 --> 01:01:16.583
Four, three, two, one.

559
01:01:16.607 --> 01:01:19.359
Harvey, we're on the air.

560
01:01:22.780 --> 01:01:24.989
Good evening.
This is Harvey Johnson.

561
01:01:26.784 --> 01:01:30.722
And I'm Gail Wallens, and this is
Nightline News at 10:00.

562
01:01:30.746 --> 01:01:33.516
Our top stories
on this Christmas Eve-

563
01:01:33.540 --> 01:01:36.626
Take truck number five
and get out of here.

564
01:01:43.592 --> 01:01:47.948
He wasn't lying about Marco.
He's down on the street.

565
01:01:47.972 --> 01:01:50.200
And the other man was Heinrich.

566
01:01:50.224 --> 01:01:53.017
And his bag is missing.

567
01:01:54.437 --> 01:01:56.938
But he had the detonators.

568
01:01:59.567 --> 01:02:01.734
Theo.

569
01:02:02.570 --> 01:02:05.298
- Theo.
- Yo!

570
01:02:05.322 --> 01:02:08.199
We may have some problems.
How's our schedule?

571
01:02:09.660 --> 01:02:14.349
- Three down, four to go.
- Then don't waste time talking to me.

572
01:02:14.373 --> 01:02:17.894
This is Sergeant Al Powell
of the Los Angeles Police Department.

573
01:02:17.918 --> 01:02:20.605
If the person who radioed for help
can hear me on this channel...

574
01:02:20.629 --> 01:02:23.734
acknowledge this transmission.

575
01:02:23.758 --> 01:02:27.154
I say again, if the person who radioed
for help on this channel can hear me...

576
01:02:27.178 --> 01:02:29.887
acknowledge this transmission.

577
01:02:34.059 --> 01:02:36.621
I read you, Powell.
You the guy in the car?

578
01:02:36.645 --> 01:02:38.665
What's left of him.

579
01:02:38.689 --> 01:02:42.711
- Can you identify yourself?
- Not now. Maybe later.

580
01:02:42.735 --> 01:02:46.423
Listen fast. This is a party line, and
the neighbors got itchy trigger fingers.

581
01:02:46.447 --> 01:02:49.926
All right, here's the deal. You got
30 or so hostages on the 30th floor.

582
01:02:49.950 --> 01:02:53.072
- The leader, his name is Hans.
- We have to find him and shut him up.

583
01:02:53.096 --> 01:02:54.697
- He's telling them everything!
- Let him.

584
01:02:54.721 --> 01:02:56.290
I'm waiting for the
FBI to arrive. Until then,

585
01:02:56.314 --> 01:03:01.062
he can waste as much time as
he likes, but we must find the bag.

586
01:03:01.086 --> 01:03:04.441
- Fritz, go help Uli. We must have the detonators.
- They got an arsenal up here.

587
01:03:04.465 --> 01:03:07.068
They got missiles, automatic weapons...

588
01:03:07.092 --> 01:03:09.154
and enough plastic explosives
to orbit Arnold Schwarzenegger.

589
01:03:09.178 --> 01:03:13.074
They're down to nine now,
countin' the skydiver you met.

590
01:03:13.098 --> 01:03:17.351
These guys are mostly European,
judging by their clothing labels and...

591
01:03:23.818 --> 01:03:25.796
cigarettes.

592
01:03:25.820 --> 01:03:28.048
They're well-financed
and very slick.

593
01:03:28.072 --> 01:03:29.523
Well how do you know that?

594
01:03:29.547 --> 01:03:31.635
I've seen enough phony ID's in my time...

595
01:03:31.659 --> 01:03:35.078
to recognize that the ones they got
must've cost a fortune.

596
01:03:37.832 --> 01:03:40.352
Add all that up, I don't know
what the fuck it means.

597
01:03:40.376 --> 01:03:44.128
But you got some badass perpetrators,
and they're here to stay.

598
01:03:45.630 --> 01:03:48.443
I hear you, partner.
L.A.'s finest are on it.

599
01:03:48.467 --> 01:03:52.470
- So light 'em if you got 'em.
- Way ahead of you, partner.

600
01:03:53.973 --> 01:03:56.224
So what do I call you?

601
01:03:57.560 --> 01:04:01.373
Call me... Roy.

602
01:04:01.397 --> 01:04:03.375
Well, listen up, Roy.

603
01:04:03.399 --> 01:04:06.670
If you think of anything else you think
we need to know, don't be shy, okay?

604
01:04:06.694 --> 01:04:09.548
In the meantime, find a safe place
to hole up and let us do our job.

605
01:04:09.572 --> 01:04:12.865
- Understand?
- They're all yours, Al.

606
01:04:30.384 --> 01:04:32.904
All right, who's talking to 'em?

607
01:04:32.928 --> 01:04:36.616
I am, sir.
Sergeant Powell. Al Powell.

608
01:04:36.640 --> 01:04:40.161
Dwayne Robinson, Powell. What's the
deal here? What do these pricks want?

609
01:04:40.185 --> 01:04:42.998
Well, if you mean the terrorists, sir,
we don't exactly know.

610
01:04:43.022 --> 01:04:45.000
We haven't heard a peep from them.

611
01:04:45.024 --> 01:04:47.711
Well, who in the hell
have you been talking to?

612
01:04:47.735 --> 01:04:50.672
We don't know that either, sir.
He won't give us his name.

613
01:04:50.696 --> 01:04:53.174
But he appears to be the one
who phoned in the report.

614
01:04:53.198 --> 01:04:56.595
He's killed one terrorist for sure,
and he claims he's capped off two others.

615
01:04:56.619 --> 01:04:58.805
He claims?

616
01:04:58.829 --> 01:05:02.559
Has it occurred to you he could be
one of the terrorists pulling your chain?

617
01:05:02.583 --> 01:05:04.811
Or some nutcase in there?

618
01:05:04.835 --> 01:05:07.564
I don't think so, sir.
In fact, I think he's a cop.

619
01:05:07.588 --> 01:05:10.332
Maybe not LAPD, but
he's definitely a badge.

620
01:05:10.356 --> 01:05:11.568
How do you know that?

621
01:05:11.592 --> 01:05:14.613
A hunch. Things he said...

622
01:05:14.637 --> 01:05:17.240
like being able to spot a phony ID

623
01:05:17.264 --> 01:05:21.411
Jesus Christ, Powell! He could be
a fucking bartender for all we know.

624
01:05:21.435 --> 01:05:25.771
- TV's here.
- Oh, shit.

625
01:05:35.950 --> 01:05:38.326
I'm not gonna warn you again.

626
01:05:42.080 --> 01:05:44.059
I have a request.

627
01:05:44.083 --> 01:05:48.563
- What idiot put you in charge?
- You did...

628
01:05:48.587 --> 01:05:50.899
when you murdered my boss.

629
01:05:50.923 --> 01:05:52.901
Now everybody's looking to me.

630
01:05:52.925 --> 01:05:58.262
Personally, I'd pass on the job.
I don't enjoy being this close to you.

631
01:06:06.355 --> 01:06:08.333
Go on.

632
01:06:08.357 --> 01:06:10.376
We have a pregnant woman out there.

633
01:06:10.400 --> 01:06:13.380
Relax. She's not due
for a couple of weeks.

634
01:06:13.404 --> 01:06:16.549
But sitting on that rock
isn't doing her back any good.

635
01:06:16.573 --> 01:06:20.284
So I would like permission to move her
to one of the offices where there's a sofa.

636
01:06:22.079 --> 01:06:24.849
No, but I'll have a sofa
brought out to you. Good enough?

637
01:06:24.873 --> 01:06:26.893
Good enough.

638
01:06:26.917 --> 01:06:30.503
And unless you like it messy, I'd start
bringing us in groups to the bathroom.

639
01:06:32.464 --> 01:06:36.152
Yes, you're right.
It will be done.

640
01:06:36.176 --> 01:06:39.178
Was there something else?

641
01:06:40.305 --> 01:06:42.515
No. Thank you.

642
01:06:48.647 --> 01:06:51.357
- Mr. Takagi chose his people well, Mrs.
-

643
01:06:52.400 --> 01:06:55.130
Gennero.

644
01:06:55.154 --> 01:06:58.239
Miss Gennero.

645
01:07:00.242 --> 01:07:02.721
We interrupt this program
for a special news bulletin.

646
01:07:02.745 --> 01:07:06.808
This is Richard Thornburg,
live from Century City.

647
01:07:06.832 --> 01:07:08.976
Tonight, Los Angeles has joined...

648
01:07:09.000 --> 01:07:12.022
the sad and worldwide
fraternity of cities...

649
01:07:12.046 --> 01:07:14.024
whose only membership requirement...

650
01:07:14.048 --> 01:07:17.276
is to suffer the anguish
of international terrorism.

651
01:07:17.300 --> 01:07:21.740
Approximately two hours ago,
an unidentified group of men...

652
01:07:21.764 --> 01:07:24.366
seized control
of the Nakatomi building...

653
01:07:24.390 --> 01:07:26.786
sealing off all entrances and exits.

654
01:07:26.810 --> 01:07:28.830
All telephone lines have been cut.

655
01:07:28.854 --> 01:07:31.206
And the only communication
now possible...

656
01:07:31.230 --> 01:07:34.461
has been through the use
of C.B. communicators...

657
01:07:34.485 --> 01:07:36.671
which the group
apparently brought with them.

658
01:07:36.695 --> 01:07:41.259
According to official sources,
the perpetrators-

659
01:07:41.283 --> 01:07:44.136
Unit Five, hold your
position at the main entrance.

660
01:07:44.160 --> 01:07:48.766
All right, guys, we got Charlie Unit
in position by the parking structure.

661
01:07:48.790 --> 01:07:52.312
Let me ask you something.
Does this stairway go up to the escalator?

662
01:07:52.336 --> 01:07:54.439
- Yeah. That's where they're going.
- Tell them to go ahead.

663
01:07:54.463 --> 01:07:55.581
Through the lobby up there

664
01:07:55.605 --> 01:07:58.651
- and try and draw some fire.
- What's going on?

665
01:07:58.675 --> 01:08:00.820
What's it look like?
We're going in.

666
01:08:00.844 --> 01:08:03.490
Goin' in? Man, that's crazy!

667
01:08:03.514 --> 01:08:06.034
There could be over 30 hostages in there
for all we know.

668
01:08:06.058 --> 01:08:08.661
We don't know shit, Powell.
If there's hostages...

669
01:08:08.685 --> 01:08:11.372
how come nobody's come to us
with ransom demands?

670
01:08:11.396 --> 01:08:15.168
If there's terrorists in there,
where's their list of demands?

671
01:08:15.192 --> 01:08:17.336
All we know is that
somebody shot your car up.

672
01:08:17.360 --> 01:08:21.341
It's probably the same silly son of a bitch
you've been talking to on that radio.

673
01:08:21.365 --> 01:08:25.470
Excuse me, sir, but what about the body
that fell out the window?

674
01:08:25.494 --> 01:08:28.515
Well, who knows? It was probably
some stockbroker who got depressed.

675
01:08:28.539 --> 01:08:31.016
- We're ready for you, Chief.
- All right, light 'em up. Let's go.

676
01:08:31.040 --> 01:08:33.520
- All right, hit your lights.
- Blue Unit, go.

677
01:08:33.544 --> 01:08:36.253
- We got approval, Chief.
- Lights on!

678
01:08:37.756 --> 01:08:39.340
Down a little.

679
01:08:47.057 --> 01:08:49.285
Al.

680
01:08:49.309 --> 01:08:51.955
Al, you still with me, babe?
What's going on?

681
01:08:51.979 --> 01:08:54.040
Yo, Al?

682
01:08:54.064 --> 01:08:57.876
I'm here, Roy. I'm kind of busy right now.
I'll talk to you later.

683
01:08:57.900 --> 01:09:00.672
- What's wrong? What's going on?
- I said I'll talk to you later.

684
01:09:00.696 --> 01:09:03.515
If you are what I think you are,
then you'll know when to listen,

685
01:09:03.539 --> 01:09:06.160
when to shut up, and--

686
01:09:06.384 --> 01:09:08.888
And when to pray.

687
01:09:08.912 --> 01:09:11.182
Jesus Christ. You're coming in.
That's it, isn't it?

688
01:09:11.206 --> 01:09:14.769
Christ, Powell, I told you what kind
of people you're dealing with here.

689
01:09:14.793 --> 01:09:17.336
- All right, let's load 'em up.
- Blue, go.

690
01:09:20.090 --> 01:09:22.986
So, they'll be coming.
Everyone get ready.

691
01:09:23.010 --> 01:09:27.012
Theo, you are the eyes now.

692
01:09:38.984 --> 01:09:40.962
- Rivers!
- Yo!

693
01:09:40.986 --> 01:09:43.756
Begin your reconnoiter.

694
01:09:43.780 --> 01:09:46.031
Let's go!

695
01:09:47.950 --> 01:09:50.411
Shit!

696
01:10:08.889 --> 01:10:11.640
Hey, come on. Let's go!

697
01:10:20.900 --> 01:10:23.068
Ow! Jesus.

698
01:10:56.937 --> 01:10:59.188
All right, spread out.

699
01:11:25.257 --> 01:11:28.194
Shut up.

700
01:11:28.218 --> 01:11:30.469
Let's go!

701
01:11:35.142 --> 01:11:37.309
You macho assholes. No! No!

702
01:11:40.063 --> 01:11:43.107
All right. Listen up, guys.

703
01:11:45.569 --> 01:11:48.923
'Twas the night before Christmas,
and all through the house...

704
01:11:48.947 --> 01:11:51.092
not a creature was stirring,
except...

705
01:11:51.116 --> 01:11:54.136
the four assholes
coming in the rear...

706
01:11:54.160 --> 01:11:56.161
in standard two-by-two
cover formation.

707
01:11:58.707 --> 01:12:01.060
Okay, we're all set.

708
01:12:01.084 --> 01:12:03.479
We're ready.

709
01:12:03.503 --> 01:12:05.690
- Kick ass.
- Go!

710
01:12:05.714 --> 01:12:07.965
Right. Let's do it.

711
01:12:23.357 --> 01:12:26.753
- Take cover!
- They're shootin' at 'em!

712
01:12:26.777 --> 01:12:28.880
It's panic fire.
They can't see anything.

713
01:12:28.904 --> 01:12:31.030
They're shootin' at the lights.

714
01:12:35.494 --> 01:12:38.871
They're going after the lights.
Pull 'em back.

715
01:12:40.165 --> 01:12:42.541
- It's not happening.
- Mike, burn it.

716
01:12:44.544 --> 01:12:46.272
Don't be impatient.

717
01:12:46.296 --> 01:12:49.435
Just wound them.

718
01:12:50.759 --> 01:12:51.293
Get 'em back.

719
01:12:51.317 --> 01:12:53.279
- They're sittin' ducks up there without lights.
- No, no, they're almost in.

720
01:12:53.303 --> 01:12:56.616
- Get 'em back!
- They're almost in. Send in the car.

721
01:12:56.640 --> 01:12:58.515
Send in the car.

722
01:13:11.613 --> 01:13:14.365
Jesus Christ!

723
01:13:16.118 --> 01:13:18.930
Rivers, Rodriguez, report.

724
01:13:18.954 --> 01:13:22.081
Whoa! Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
What have we here, gentlemen?

725
01:13:25.919 --> 01:13:28.796
The police have themselves an R.V.

726
01:13:33.885 --> 01:13:36.512
Southeast corner.

727
01:13:37.347 --> 01:13:40.015
Hurry...

728
01:13:48.233 --> 01:13:50.442
Oh, Jesus Christ.

729
01:14:02.122 --> 01:14:05.082
Out of here! Get back!
Get the fuck back!

730
01:14:06.626 --> 01:14:09.962
- Get over there!
- Hurry.

731
01:14:12.052 --> 01:14:16.302
