with them in prison.

961
01:29:27.296 --> 01:29:29.816
No, no.
No, darling. "Asian Dawn."

962
01:29:29.840 --> 01:29:33.528
Dawn. D-A-W-N.

963
01:29:33.552 --> 01:29:35.530
- Sir?
- I - Yeah?

964
01:29:35.554 --> 01:29:38.450
- The FBI is here.
- Oh. The FBI is here now?

965
01:29:38.474 --> 01:29:40.452
Yes, sir, right over there.

966
01:29:40.476 --> 01:29:44.062
- Hold this.
- You want a breath mint?

967
01:29:46.190 --> 01:29:48.502
Uh, yeah. We got it.

968
01:29:48.526 --> 01:29:51.129
Hey! How you doing, man?

969
01:29:51.153 --> 01:29:53.673
I'm Agent Johnson.
This is Special Agent Johnson.

970
01:29:53.697 --> 01:29:56.968
- Oh. How you doing?
- No relation.

971
01:29:56.992 --> 01:29:59.846
I'm, uh -

972
01:29:59.870 --> 01:30:03.725
I'm Dwayne Robinson, LAPD
I'm in charge here.

973
01:30:03.749 --> 01:30:06.000
Not anymore.

974
01:30:59.889 --> 01:31:04.267
Hi, there. How you doing?

975
01:31:07.520 --> 01:31:10.041
Oh!

976
01:31:10.065 --> 01:31:15.172
Please, God, no. You're one of them,
aren't you? You're one of them.

977
01:31:15.196 --> 01:31:17.799
Don't - Don't kill me.
Please, don't. Please!

978
01:31:17.823 --> 01:31:20.552
- Don't kill me. Don't kill me, please.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

979
01:31:20.576 --> 01:31:25.163
Relax. Relax. I'm not gonna hurt you.
I'm not gonna hurt you!

980
01:31:27.750 --> 01:31:29.959
Oh, God.

981
01:31:32.755 --> 01:31:35.901
What the fuck are you doing up here?
What were you looking for?

982
01:31:35.925 --> 01:31:39.613
I managed to get out of there,
and, uh -

983
01:31:39.637 --> 01:31:41.906
Well, I was just trying
to get up on the roof...

984
01:31:41.930 --> 01:31:45.869
and see if I could
signal for help, you know.

985
01:31:45.893 --> 01:31:47.954
It's just through here.
Why don't you come and help -

986
01:31:47.978 --> 01:31:51.666
- Whoa, whoa, whoa. Forget the roof.
- Come on. Come on.

987
01:31:51.690 --> 01:31:56.171
I said forget the roof.
They got people all over it.

988
01:31:56.195 --> 01:31:58.696
Come on. You wanna stay alive,
you stay with me.

989
01:32:01.367 --> 01:32:03.720
Well, the best way
we can figure it is...

990
01:32:03.744 --> 01:32:07.140
we've got maybe
30 or 35 hostages up there...

991
01:32:07.164 --> 01:32:09.142
probably on the 30th floor...

992
01:32:09.166 --> 01:32:12.771
and maybe, I don't know,
seven or eight terrorists up there.

993
01:32:12.795 --> 01:32:15.148
Sounds like an A-7 scenario.

994
01:32:15.172 --> 01:32:17.234
Thank you.
We'll handle it from here.

995
01:32:17.258 --> 01:32:20.612
When we commandeer your men,
we'll try and let you know.

996
01:32:20.636 --> 01:32:23.323
- Aren't you forgetting something?
- Such as?

997
01:32:23.347 --> 01:32:25.325
What about John McClane?

998
01:32:25.349 --> 01:32:28.536
He's the reason why we have
the information we have up until now.

999
01:32:28.560 --> 01:32:32.249
He's also the reason why you're facing
seven terrorists instead of 12.

1000
01:32:32.273 --> 01:32:34.668
He's inside? Who is he?

1001
01:32:34.692 --> 01:32:37.629
Well, he might be a cop.
I don't know. We're checking on that.

1002
01:32:37.653 --> 01:32:40.571
- One of yours?
- No. No way.

1003
01:32:44.326 --> 01:32:47.036
Do you smoke?

1004
01:32:47.870 --> 01:32:50.081
Yeah.

1005
01:32:54.628 --> 01:32:56.879
Thanks.

1006
01:33:00.426 --> 01:33:03.719
You don't work for Nakatomi.

1007
01:33:06.640 --> 01:33:08.808
And if you're not one of them -

1008
01:33:11.270 --> 01:33:13.437
I'm a cop from New York.

1009
01:33:14.773 --> 01:33:16.751
New York?

1010
01:33:16.775 --> 01:33:18.836
Yeah.

1011
01:33:18.860 --> 01:33:23.239
Got invited to the Christmas
party by mistake. Who knew?

1012
01:33:28.912 --> 01:33:31.766
Yeah.

1013
01:33:31.790 --> 01:33:34.917
It's better than being caught
with your pants down, huh?

1014
01:33:41.884 --> 01:33:44.635
I'm John McClane.

1015
01:33:46.013 --> 01:33:47.763
You're, uh -

1016
01:33:48.724 --> 01:33:51.620
Clay.

1017
01:33:51.644 --> 01:33:53.811
Bill Clay.

1018
01:33:59.735 --> 01:34:02.028
You know how to use a handgun, Bill?

1019
01:34:03.238 --> 01:34:05.216
I spent a weekend at a combat ranch.

1020
01:34:05.240 --> 01:34:07.636
You know that game
with the guns that shoot red paint?

1021
01:34:07.660 --> 01:34:11.037
Probably seems
kind of stupid to you.

1022
01:34:11.789 --> 01:34:14.040
Well...

1023
01:34:15.500 --> 01:34:17.668
time for the real thing, Bill.

1024
01:34:26.010 --> 01:34:29.805
All you gotta do
is pull the trigger. Come on.

1025
01:34:38.273 --> 01:34:40.691
33rd. floor. Come right away.

1026
01:34:48.992 --> 01:34:51.136
Put down the gun...

1027
01:34:51.160 --> 01:34:53.537
and give me my detonators.

1028
01:34:57.793 --> 01:35:02.148
Well, well, well. Hans.

1029
01:35:02.172 --> 01:35:05.925
Put it down now.

1030
01:35:09.596 --> 01:35:13.118
That's pretty tricky
with that accent.

1031
01:35:13.142 --> 01:35:15.601
You oughta be on fucking TV
with that accent.

1032
01:35:18.355 --> 01:35:22.085
But what do you want
with the detonators, Hans?

1033
01:35:22.109 --> 01:35:26.464
I already used all the explosives.

1034
01:35:26.488 --> 01:35:28.698
Or did I?

1035
01:35:30.159 --> 01:35:32.220
- I'm going to count to three.
- Yeah.

1036
01:35:32.244 --> 01:35:34.889
Like you did with Takagi?

1037
01:35:34.913 --> 01:35:37.726
Oops.

1038
01:35:37.750 --> 01:35:41.229
No bullets. You think
I'm fucking stupid, Hans?

1039
01:35:41.253 --> 01:35:43.629
You were saying?

1040
01:36:36.517 --> 01:36:39.536
Karl.

1041
01:36:39.560 --> 01:36:43.647
Shoot the Windows!

1042
01:36:47.486 --> 01:36:50.488
Shoot the glass.

1043
01:37:23.814 --> 01:37:26.023
Jesus Christ!

1044
01:37:54.510 --> 01:37:57.555
Smile, Karl.
We're back in business.

1045
01:38:00.017 --> 01:38:03.496
Is the last resort of diplomacy.

1046
01:38:03.520 --> 01:38:06.332
Then couldn't we just as well say...

1047
01:38:06.356 --> 01:38:09.168
that terrorism has an equal claim
on being that too?

1048
01:38:09.192 --> 01:38:12.046
You got something.
Tell me you got something.

1049
01:38:12.070 --> 01:38:14.924
Just McClane's name, badge number,
employment record...

1050
01:38:14.948 --> 01:38:17.594
vital statistics
and his family's home address...

1051
01:38:17.618 --> 01:38:20.138
right here in L.A.

1052
01:38:20.162 --> 01:38:22.955
Whoa!

1053
01:38:27.836 --> 01:38:29.689
Go to work.

1054
01:38:29.713 --> 01:38:31.964
Got it.

1055
01:38:43.769 --> 01:38:47.855
God, that man looks really pissed.

1056
01:38:49.149 --> 01:38:53.880
- He's still alive.
- What?

1057
01:38:53.904 --> 01:38:58.157
Only John can drive
somebody that crazy.

1058
01:39:12.798 --> 01:39:15.526
Hans.

1059
01:39:15.550 --> 01:39:18.154
You better heat up that miracle, because
we just broke through on number six...

1060
01:39:18.178 --> 01:39:20.949
and the electromagnetic
came down like a fucking anvil.

1061
01:39:20.973 --> 01:39:26.518
Have a look at what our friends outside
are doing, and I'll be right up.

1062
01:39:28.730 --> 01:39:32.210
Hey, John?
John McClane, you still with us?

1063
01:39:32.234 --> 01:39:34.212
Yeah.

1064
01:39:34.236 --> 01:39:38.072
But all things being equal,
I'd rather be in Philadelphia.

1065
01:39:38.907 --> 01:39:41.594
Chalk up two more bad guys.

1066
01:39:41.618 --> 01:39:44.370
Well, the boys down here
will be glad to hear that.

1067
01:39:45.247 --> 01:39:47.475
You know, we got
a pool going on you.

1068
01:39:47.499 --> 01:39:50.812
- What kind of odds am I gettin'?
- You don't want to know.

1069
01:39:50.836 --> 01:39:54.713
Put me down for 20.
I'm good for it.

1070
01:39:57.259 --> 01:40:00.719
Hey, Powell, you got flat feet?

1071
01:40:02.597 --> 01:40:04.659
What the hell
you talking about, man?

1072
01:40:04.683 --> 01:40:07.662
Something had to
get you off the street.

1073
01:40:07.686 --> 01:40:10.248
What's the matter? You don't think
jockeying papers across a desk...

1074
01:40:10.272 --> 01:40:13.023
is a noble effort for a cop?

1075
01:40:14.234 --> 01:40:16.485
No.

1076
01:40:18.739 --> 01:40:22.676
- I had an accident.
- The way you drive, I can see why.

1077
01:40:22.700 --> 01:40:26.537
What'd you do, run over
your captain's foot with a car?

1078
01:40:29.416 --> 01:40:31.583
I shot a kid.

1079
01:40:33.128 --> 01:40:36.606
He was 13 years old.

1080
01:40:36.630 --> 01:40:39.110
It was dark. I couldn't see him.
He had a ray gun.

1081
01:40:39.134 --> 01:40:41.385
It looked real enough.

1082
01:40:43.472 --> 01:40:46.576
You know, when you're a rookie, they can
teach you everything about being a cop...

1083
01:40:46.600 --> 01:40:49.268
except how to live with a mistake.

1084
01:40:53.148 --> 01:40:57.484
Anyway, I just couldn't bring myself
to draw my gun on anybody again.

1085
01:41:00.989 --> 01:41:03.801
Sorry, man.

1086
01:41:03.825 --> 01:41:06.702
Hey, man, how could you know?

1087
01:41:08.830 --> 01:41:11.915
I feel like shit anyway.

1088
01:41:13.293 --> 01:41:15.271
Well, then this won't matter.

1089
01:41:15.295 --> 01:41:20.257
The LAPD is not calling
the shots down here anymore.

1090
01:41:22.510 --> 01:41:25.554
- Feds?
- You got it.

1091
01:41:26.848 --> 01:41:30.059
All right, those
are the city engineers.

1092
01:41:31.937 --> 01:41:33.915
They're going into
the street circuits.

1093
01:41:33.939 --> 01:41:36.766
Those guys in the suits -
I don't know who they are.

1094
01:41:36.790 --> 01:41:38.233
That's the FBI

1095
01:41:39.360 --> 01:41:42.506
They're ordering the others
to cut the building's power.

1096
01:41:42.530 --> 01:41:44.782
Regular as clockwork.

1097
01:41:46.243 --> 01:41:50.306
- Or a time lock.
- Precisely.

1098
01:41:50.330 --> 01:41:54.352
The circuits that cannot be cut
are cut automatically...

1099
01:41:54.376 --> 01:41:57.230
in response to a terrorist incident.

1100
01:41:57.254 --> 01:42:00.024
You asked for miracles, Theo.
I give you...

1101
01:42:00.048 --> 01:42:03.528
the FBI

1102
01:42:03.552 --> 01:42:05.295
I said I want the friggin'
building shut down.

1103
01:42:05.319 --> 01:42:07.115
- I got a problem.
- I don't care what your problem--

1104
01:42:07.139 --> 01:42:10.034
- I got a switch here -
- I don't give two shits about your switch!

1105
01:42:10.058 --> 01:42:13.162
- I want the building out. Dark. D-A-R-K!
- Hold on! You don't understand.

1106
01:42:13.186 --> 01:42:15.164
- You can't do it from here.
- Yeah, you could.

1107
01:42:15.188 --> 01:42:16.874
It can't be done from here.

1108
01:42:16.898 --> 01:42:17.932
I could just - I got the radio.

1109
01:42:17.956 --> 01:42:20.002
You can't do it from
down here I'm telling you.

1110
01:42:20.026 --> 01:42:22.296
It's gotta be done from downtown.

1111
01:42:22.320 --> 01:42:24.298
They've gotta take out
a whole city grid.

1112
01:42:24.322 --> 01:42:26.843
- We're talking 10 square blocks.
- Ten blocks?

1113
01:42:26.867 --> 01:42:28.845
Johnson, that's crazy.
It's Christmas Eve, man.

1114
01:42:28.869 --> 01:42:32.473
- There's thousands of people.
- You have to go wider.

1115
01:42:32.497 --> 01:42:34.475
- I need authorization.
- Authorization?

1116
01:42:34.499 --> 01:42:36.284
How about the United
States fucking government?

1117
01:42:36.308 --> 01:42:37.353
Hey.

1118
01:42:37.377 --> 01:42:40.003
Lose the grid or you lose your job.

1119
01:42:46.094 --> 01:42:48.072
- Yeah, Central?
- Yeah?

1120
01:42:48.096 --> 01:42:51.616
This is Walt down at Nakatomi.
Say, listen.

1121
01:42:51.640 --> 01:42:55.580
Would it be possible
for you to turn off grid 212?

1122
01:42:55.604 --> 01:42:59.166
- Are you crazy?
- Maybe I should call the mayor.

1123
01:42:59.190 --> 01:43:02.253
No shit, it's my ass. I got a big problem
down here. Shut it down.

1124
01:43:02.277 --> 01:43:04.987
Shut it down now.

1125
01:43:07.407 --> 01:43:11.012
Emergency lighting activated.

1126
01:43:11.036 --> 01:43:13.530
Powell. Powell, talk to
me. What's going on here?

1127
01:43:13.554 --> 01:43:15.391
Ask the FBI.

1128
01:43:15.415 --> 01:43:18.226
They got the universal
terrorist playbook...

1129
01:43:18.250 --> 01:43:20.878
and they're running it step by step.

1130
01:43:22.797 --> 01:43:24.775
It's gonna go. It's gonna go!

1131
01:43:24.799 --> 01:43:28.177
Yes!

1132
01:43:50.700 --> 01:43:52.951
Merry Christmas.

1133
01:43:54.829 --> 01:43:56.933
Those bastards are probably
pissing in their pants right now.

1134
01:43:56.957 --> 01:43:59.124
The mayor's gonna have my ass.

1135
01:44:06.132 --> 01:44:08.383
Whoo!

1136
01:44:20.230 --> 01:44:23.542
Well, what are we gonna do now?

1137
01:44:23.566 --> 01:44:26.045
Arrest them for not
paying their electric bill?

1138
01:44:26.069 --> 01:44:31.008
We've shut them down. We let 'em sweat
for a while, then we give 'em helicopters.

1139
01:44:31.032 --> 01:44:33.283
Right up the ass.

1140
01:44:36.079 --> 01:44:39.350
This is Agent Johnson.
No, the other one.

1141
01:44:39.374 --> 01:44:42.520
I want that air support
ready to lift off in five minutes.

1142
01:44:42.544 --> 01:44:46.004
Damn right. Fully armed.
We're on the way.

1143
01:44:50.050 --> 01:44:53.804
Oh, yeah!

1144
01:44:55.557 --> 01:44:57.975
I wish to talk to the FBI

1145
01:45:00.520 --> 01:45:02.498
This is Special Agent Johnson
of the FBI

1146
01:45:02.522 --> 01:45:07.044
The State Department has arranged
for the return of your comrades.

1147
01:45:07.068 --> 01:45:09.839
Helicopters are en route
as you requested.

1148
01:45:09.863 --> 01:45:11.841
I hear you. We'll be ready.

1149
01:45:11.865 --> 01:45:14.593
By the time he figures out
what hit him, he'll be in a body bag.

1150
01:45:14.617 --> 01:45:16.679
When they touch down,
we'll blow the roof.

1151
01:45:16.703 --> 01:45:18.723
They'll spend a month
sifting through the rubble.

1152
01:45:18.747 --> 01:45:21.225
And by the time they figure out
what went wrong...

1153
01:45:21.249 --> 01:45:24.835
we'll be sitting on a beach
earning 20%.

1154
01:45:29.466 --> 01:45:32.736
Powell.

1155
01:45:32.760 --> 01:45:35.012
Yo, Powell, you got a minute?

1156
01:45:36.264 --> 01:45:38.473
I'm here, John.

1157
01:45:40.143 --> 01:45:43.622
Listen, man, I'm starting
to get a bad feeling up here.

1158
01:45:43.646 --> 01:45:45.875
I want you to do something for me.

1159
01:45:45.899 --> 01:45:48.544
Um -

1160
01:45:48.568 --> 01:45:52.756
I want you to find my wife.
Don't ask me how. By then, you'll know how.

1161
01:45:52.780 --> 01:45:57.303
Uh, I want you
to tell her something.

1162
01:45:57.327 --> 01:45:59.846
I want you to tell her that...

1163
01:45:59.870 --> 01:46:02.122
um -

1164
01:46:06.127 --> 01:46:09.273
Tell her it took me
a while to figure out...

1165
01:46:09.297 --> 01:46:13.258
what a jerk I've been, but, um -

1166
01:46:14.302 --> 01:46:16.553
but that -

1167
01:46:19.474 --> 01:46:22.078
that when things
started to pan out for her...

1168
01:46:22.102 --> 01:46:27.606
I should've been
more supportive, and, uh -

1169
01:46:28.942 --> 01:46:31.652
and I just should've been
behind her more.

1170
01:46:33.488 --> 01:46:36.573
Oh, shit.

1171
01:46:38.827 --> 01:46:42.098
Tell her that, um -

1172
01:46:42.122 --> 01:46:46.291
that she's the best thing that
ever happened to a bum like me.

1173
01:46:48.169 --> 01:46:51.922
She's heard me say "I love you"
a thousand times.

1174
01:46:53.174 --> 01:46:55.592
She never heard me say, "I'm sorry."

1175
01:46:56.928 --> 01:47:00.825
And I want you to tell her that.
I want you to tell her that...

1176
01:47:00.849 --> 01:47:04.328
John said that he was sorry.

1177
01:47:04.352 --> 01:47:06.539
Okay?

1178
01:47:06.563 --> 01:47:10.107
- You got that, man?
- Yeah, I got it, John.

1179
01:47:11.192 --> 01:47:14.171
But you can tell her that yourself.

1180
01:47:14.195 --> 01:47:18.342
You just watch your ass and you'll
make it out of there. You hear me?

1181
01:47:18.366 --> 01:47:20.826
Well, I guess that's up
to the man upstairs.

1182
01:47:24.372 --> 01:47:28.310
John? John?

1183
01:47:28.334 --> 01:47:31.253
What the fuck were
you doing upstairs, Hans?

1184
01:47:33.548 --> 01:47:34.282
John?

1185
01:47:34.306 --> 01:47:37.926
No, Al, listen. Listen,
just lay off for a while.

1186
01:47:39.720 --> 01:47:41.972
I gotta go check on something.

1187
01:47:45.059 --> 01:47:47.788
One minute.
That's all I'm asking.

1188
01:47:47.812 --> 01:47:50.541
One minute just to speak to you.
All right. All right.

1189
01:47:50.565 --> 01:47:54.086
All right. Get back.
Get back. Off. Off. All right.

1190
01:47:54.110 --> 01:47:57.381
Look, you let me in right now,
or I call the I.N.S.

1191
01:47:57.405 --> 01:48:00.092
Comprende?

1192
01:48:00.116 --> 01:48:05.454
Look, this is the last time these kids
are gonna have to speak to their parents.

1193
01:48:07.332 --> 01:48:11.168
All right? All right.
Come on. Come on.

1194
01:48:21.638 --> 01:48:25.432
What were you doing, Hans?
What were you doing?

1195
01:48:47.455 --> 01:48:50.499
Jesus, Mary, mother of God.

1196
01:48:53.878 --> 01:48:56.106
Powell, listen to me!
It's a double cross!

1197
01:48:56.130 --> 01:48:58.715
The whole roof
of the building's wired to -

1198
01:49:01.177 --> 01:49:03.428
John.

1199
01:49:04.222 --> 01:49:06.200
John.

1200
01:49:06.224 --> 01:49:09.119
John, come in. Did you get that?

1201
01:49:09.143 --> 01:49:11.895
No. Something about a double cross.

1202
01:49:12.647 --> 01:49:14.856
Tell me about it.

1203
01:49:20.446 --> 01:49:22.781
We are both professionals.

1204
01:49:24.867 --> 01:49:27.805
This is personal.

1205
01:49:27.829 --> 01:49:30.455
Oh.

1206
01:49:50.018 --> 01:49:53.080
They're coming.

1207
01:49:53.104 --> 01:49:55.082
- Choppers are coming.
- Okay.

1208
01:49:55.106 --> 01:49:59.086
Time to gather your flock,
Miss Gennero.

1209
01:49:59.110 --> 01:50:01.505
You know, your mom
and dad are very important people.

1210
01:50:01.529 --> 01:50:04.842
They're very brave people.

1211
01:50:04.866 --> 01:50:08.410
So is there something you would like
to say to them if they're watching?

1212
01:50:09.245 --> 01:50:11.997
Come home.

1213
01:50:18.713 --> 01:50:21.798
Mrs. McClane.

1214
01:50:25.053 --> 01:50:29.014
How nice to make your acquaintance.

1215
01:50:31.726 --> 01:50:33.704
On your feet, everyone!
To the roof!

1216
01:50:33.728 --> 01:50:36.771
Lock them up there
and come right back.

1217
01:50:38.440 --> 01:50:40.692
Move! Come on! Let's move!

1218
01:51:05.093 --> 01:51:09.596
You should've heard your brother squeal
when I broke his fucking neck!

1219
01:51:12.642 --> 01:51:15.286
What do you figure the breakage?

1220
01:51:15.310 --> 01:51:17.373
Figure we take out the terrorists...

1221
01:51:17.397 --> 01:51:21.085
lose 20-25% of the hostages... tops.

1222
01:51:21.109 --> 01:51:23.629
I can live with that.

1223
01:51:23.653 --> 01:51:28.740
Keep this thing on the deck.
They're expecting transports, not gunships.

1224
01:51:40.420 --> 01:51:44.108
Move it! Come on! Move!
Come on! Come on!

1225
01:51:44.132 --> 01:51:46.694
Move it!

1226
01:51:46.718 --> 01:51:49.761
Let's go! Move!

1227
01:51:52.056 --> 01:51:54.993
Theo. A little bonus for us.

1228
01:51:55.017 --> 01:51:57.830
- Please, sit down. Sit down.
- Hey!

1229
01:51:57.854 --> 01:51:59.956
A policeman's wife
might come in handy.

1230
01:51:59.980 --> 01:52:03.626
McClane, I have some news for you.

1231
01:52:03.650 --> 01:52:06.027
McClane.

1232
01:52:16.080 --> 01:52:18.331
Come on! Move, move!

1233
01:52:20.209 --> 01:52:22.419
Come on!

1234
01:52:33.806 --> 01:52:36.182
Motherfucker, I'll kill you!

1235
01:52:39.187 --> 01:52:42.416
Armed. The truck?

1236
01:52:42.440 --> 01:52:44.691
The truck.

1237
01:52:50.948 --> 01:52:54.678
After all your posturing,
all your little speeches...

1238
01:52:54.702 --> 01:52:57.346
you're nothing but a common thief.

1239
01:52:57.370 --> 01:53:00.142
I am an exceptional thief,
Mrs. McClane.

1240
01:53:00.166 --> 01:53:03.626
And since I'm moving up to kidnapping,
you should be more polite.

1241
01:53:10.676 --> 01:53:12.863
Motherfucker, I'm gonna kill you!

1242
01:53:12.887 --> 01:53:16.598
I'm gonna fucking cook you,
and I'm gonna fucking eat you!

1243
01:53:38.955 --> 01:53:41.289
I don't like this, Sarge.

1244
01:53:51.759 --> 01:53:55.345
Just like fuckin' Saigon, eh, slick?

1245
01:53:56.597 --> 01:53:59.349
I was in junior high, dickhead.

1246
01:54:27.587 --> 01:54:30.440
Where's Holly?
Where's Holly Gennero?

1247
01:54:30.464 --> 01:54:34.194
Holly Gennero! Where's Holly?
Where's Holly? Where is she?

1248
01:54:34.218 --> 01:54:35.863
- They took her!
- Where?

1249
01:54:35.887 --> 01:54:37.739
- The vault!
- Where is the vault?

1250
01:54:37.763 --> 01:54:42.369
The 30th floor. Up the stairs.
They just took her!

1251
01:54:42.393 --> 01:54:46.623
Get downstairs, all of you! The whole
fuckin' roof is wired to blow. Get down!

1252
01:54:46.647 --> 01:54:51.461
Get down! Get the fuck downstairs!

1253
01:54:51.485 --> 01:54:52.645
They made us, Bureau.

1254
01:54:52.669 --> 01:54:55.196
- You got a terrorist shooting hostages.
- I see it. Bank left.

1255
01:55:02.370 --> 01:55:05.415
Nail that sucker!

1256
01:55:12.173 --> 01:55:15.276
I'm on your side, you assholes!

1257
01:55:15.300 --> 01:55:18.636
Shit. Swing around again!
I'll bag this little bastard.

1258
01:55:38.032 --> 01:55:40.783
What the fuck - Jesus!

1259
01:55:42.119 --> 01:55:44.514
Oh, John, what the fuck
are you doing?

1260
01:55:44.538 --> 01:55:47.498
How the fuck
did you get into this shit?

1261
01:55:56.968 --> 01:56:00.446
There's something wrong.
They're coming back down.

1262
01:56:00.470 --> 01:56:02.866
- Blow the roof.
- But Karl's up there!

1263
01:56:02.890 --> 01:56:05.475
Blow the roof!

1264
01:56:07.395 --> 01:56:10.540
I promise I will never even think...

1265
01:56:10.564 --> 01:56:13.608
about going up
in a tall building again.

1266
01:56:16.570 --> 01:56:19.322
Oh, God.
Please don't let me die.

1267
01:56:31.585 --> 01:56:34.337
Holy shit!

1268
01:57:50.706 --> 01:57:53.499
Holy Christ!

1269
01:57:54.418 --> 01:57:57.170
We're gonna need some more
FBI guys, I guess.

1270
01:58:09.725 --> 01:58:12.060
Jesus fucking Christ!

1271
01:58:38.045 --> 01:58:40.797
What the fuck is going on?

1272
01:58:42.716 --> 01:58:46.386
What are you gonna do, sit here while
the building falls down around your ears?

1273
01:58:53.477 --> 01:58:55.288
Shit!

1274
01:58:55.312 --> 01:58:58.022
Hey! All right!

1275
01:59:01.152 --> 01:59:06.614
Hang on, baby.
Hang on, honey. Oh, God.

1276
01:59:51.493 --> 01:59:53.411
Hans!

1277
02:00:07.176 --> 02:00:09.529
Jesus.

1278
02:00:09.553 --> 02:00:11.929
Hi, honey.

1279
02:00:34.078 --> 02:00:36.056
So that's what this was all about?

1280
02:00:36.080 --> 02:00:39.749
- A fucking robbery?
- Put down the gun.

1281
02:00:41.585 --> 02:00:43.563
Why did you have to nuke
the whole building, Hans?

1282
02:00:43.587 --> 02:00:46.691
When you steal $600,
you can just disappear.

1283
02:00:46.715 --> 02:00:49.819
When you steal 600 million,
they will find you...

1284
02:00:49.843 --> 02:00:52.322
unless they think
you're already dead.

1285
02:00:52.346 --> 02:00:54.555
Put down the gun.

1286
02:01:04.775 --> 02:01:08.380
Nein (No)! This is mine.

1287
02:01:08.404 --> 02:01:11.758
You got me.

1288
02:01:11.782 --> 02:01:14.469
Still the cowboy, Mr. McClane.

1289
02:01:14.493 --> 02:01:16.805
Americans, all alike.
Well, this time...

1290
02:01:16.829 --> 02:01:20.266
John Wayne does not
walk off into the sunset with Grace Kelly.

1291
02:01:20.290 --> 02:01:22.185
That's Gary Cooper, asshole.

1292
02:01:22.209 --> 02:01:24.062
Enough jokes.

1293
02:01:24.086 --> 02:01:27.023
You'd have made a pretty good
cowboy yourself, Hans.

1294
02:01:27.047 --> 02:01:31.778
Oh, yes.
What was it you said to me before?

1295
02:01:31.802 --> 02:01:37.265
Yippee-ki-yea, motherfucker.

1296
02:01:56.327 --> 02:01:58.452
Holly!

1297
02:02:03.375 --> 02:02:06.419
Happy trails, Hans.

1298
02:02:49.170 --> 02:02:51.547
I hope that's not a hostage.

1299
02:03:19.952 --> 02:03:24.246
Give me water hook-ups for engine
companies five, three, nine, six.

1300
02:03:27.626 --> 02:03:30.271
Over here. It's a better angle.

1301
02:03:30.295 --> 02:03:33.005
Let's give 'em a hand over there.

1302
02:03:34.383 --> 02:03:36.842
Keep it going now.
Keep it going.

1303
02:03:42.140 --> 02:03:44.119
Come on. Come on!
We're gonna miss it.

1304
02:03:44.143 --> 02:03:46.246
- Okay, hand me my notes.
- Come on!

1305
02:03:46.270 --> 02:03:49.021
Keep that water on there.

1306
02:04:08.500 --> 02:04:11.938
What was it like in there? How did they
treat you? Did they frighten you at all?

1307
02:04:11.962 --> 02:04:14.274
- Any comment?
- We don't wanna talk about it.

1308
02:04:14.298 --> 02:04:17.800
How does it feel to be outside?

1309
02:04:59.050 --> 02:05:01.070
Al, this is my wife Holly.

1310
02:05:01.094 --> 02:05:03.364
Holly Gennero.

1311
02:05:03.388 --> 02:05:06.868
- Holly McClane.
- Hello, Holly.

1312
02:05:06.892 --> 02:05:11.122
You got yourself a good man.
You take good care of him.

1313
02:05:11.146 --> 02:05:13.208
- McClane?
- Yeah, it's okay. Let him through.

1314
02:05:13.232 --> 02:05:15.335
McClane, I wanna debrief.

1315
02:05:15.359 --> 02:05:19.172
I want a debriefing.
You got some things to answer for, mister.

1316
02:05:19.196 --> 02:05:22.258
Ellis's murder, for one thing.
Property damage.

1317
02:05:22.282 --> 02:05:24.617
Interfering with police business.

1318
02:06:04.783 --> 02:06:08.054
All right, I want two of you to go
inside and see if there's anybody else.

1319
02:06:08.078 --> 02:06:10.371
Yes, sir. I'll take the left.

1320
02:06:17.713 --> 02:06:21.423
- Watch it!
- Whoa. This one's with me.

1321
02:06:28.180 --> 02:06:31.536
Five, four, three, two.

1322
02:06:31.560 --> 02:06:34.205
Mr. McClane. Mr. McClane,
now that it's all over...

1323
02:06:34.229 --> 02:06:37.731
after this incredible ordeal,
what are your feelings?

1324
02:06:42.779 --> 02:06:45.133
Well, well, well.

1325
02:06:45.157 --> 02:06:48.117
- Merry Christmas, Argyle.
- Merry Christmas.

1326
02:06:50.996 --> 02:06:52.974
Did you get that?

1327
02:06:52.998 --> 02:06:56.102
Let me through.
Let me through. Thank you.

1328
02:06:56.126 --> 02:07:00.129
If this is their idea of Christmas,
I gotta be here for New Year's.

